<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=7745&amp;p=78221#p78221"><![CDATA[
<div class="quotetitle">qbradq wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><br />Hey Drag, can you cut that Duck Tales patch down to three Game Genie codes? If so I'd love you lots <img src="http://forums.nesdev.com/images/smilies/icon_wink.gif" alt=":wink:" title="Wink" /><br /></div><br />It's funny because I had to change exactly 3 bytes to get it working. <img src="http://forums.nesdev.com/images/smilies/icon_razz.gif" alt=":P" title="Razz" /><br />However, just changing those 3 bytes effectively disables your ability to do a midair golf swing (push against a wall, jump while still pushing against the wall, and hit B in midair). In order to allow simplified pogo jumping while preserving your ability to do a midair golf swing, I had to rearrange a routine as well as change those 3 bytes. :\<br /><br />Edit:<br />I don't know how to encode these, but:<br />E68A = 04 -&gt; 40<br />EA27 = 44 -&gt; 40<br />EA29 = 44 -&gt; 40<br /><br />That should make your life easier, but like I said, if you want simplified pogo + midair golf swings, you'll need <a href="http://www.romhacking.net/hacks/749/" class="postlink">this</a>.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=21">Drag</a> — Sun May 15, 2011 6:18 pm</p><hr />
